<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>A lightweight, easy-to-use editor.</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1><title>Options</title>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
  <term><option>-h</option></term>
  <listitem>
    <para>display help information and exit</para>
  </listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
  <term><option>-V</option></term>
  <listitem>
    <para>print version information and exit</para>
  </listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</refsect1>

<refsect1><title>Configuration</title>
  <para>&iv; draws its configuration from four sources: defaults built into
    the program, the settings in /etc/iv, the settings in ~/.iv, and
    (optionally) the settings in the directory specified by IV_CONFDIR.</para>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
  <term><filename>sample.dat</filename></term>
  <listitem>
    <para>sample data is used</para>
  </listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</refsect1> <!-- OPTIONS -->

<refsect1><title>Environment</title>
<para>A few environment variables dictate IV's behavior.</para>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
  <term>IV_CONFDIR</term>
  <listitem>
    <para>Sets another directory from which to read configuration, in addition
      to the defaults.</para>
  </listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</refsect1> <!-- ENVIRONMENT -->

